## Non-Negotiables

- Keep code complete for the selected stack.
- Do not add code for unselected technologies.
- Do not add dependencies, imports, modules, providers, environment variables, Docker services, Prisma models, Redis integrations, Swagger decorators, or queue wiring unless that feature is selected or explicitly requested.
- Preserve the generated architecture style and module layout.
- Prefer small, behavior-preserving refactors unless the user asks for a redesign.
- Use `<%= packageManagerName %>` commands only: install with `<%= pmInstallCommand %>` and run scripts with `<%= pmRunCommandPrefix %> script-name`.

## Selected-Stack Rules

<%_ if (selections.architecture === 'standard') { _%>
- Use standard NestJS modules under `src/<feature>`.
- Keep controllers thin and services responsible for business behavior.
<%_ } else if (selections.architecture === 'clean') { _%>
- Keep presentation, application, and infrastructure boundaries intact.
- Application code should depend on ports, not concrete infrastructure adapters.
<%_ } else if (selections.architecture === 'ddd') { _%>
- Keep domain logic framework-agnostic under `domain`.
- Put use cases and ports in `application`, adapters in `infrastructure`, and HTTP code in `presentation`.
<%_ } _%>
<%_ if (selections.orm === 'prisma') { _%>
- Prisma is selected. Use `PrismaService`, Prisma generated types, and `prisma/schema.prisma`.
- For new Prisma models, prefer `createdAt @map("created_at")`, `updatedAt @map("updated_at")`, and `deletedAt @map("deleted_at")`; query active business records with `deletedAt: null`.
- Never add TypeORM or Sequelize.
<%_ } else if (selections.orm === 'typeorm') { _%>
- TypeORM is selected. Use `TypeOrmModule` and TypeORM entities.
- Prefer explicit snake_case column names, audit columns, migrations, and soft delete for business records.
- Never add Prisma or Sequelize.
<%_ } else if (selections.orm === 'sequelize') { _%>
- Sequelize is selected. Use `SequelizeModule` and Sequelize models.
- Prefer explicit table/column names, timestamps, and paranoid soft delete for business records.
- Never add Prisma or TypeORM.
<%_ } else { _%>
- No ORM is selected. Do not introduce persistence code unless requested.
<%_ } _%>
<%_ if (selectedOptionIds.includes('redis')) { _%>
